==Old English==
===Etymology===
From West Germanic ''*wargian-'', from Germanic ''*wargaz'' ‘wolf’ (Old English [[wearg]]).  Cognate with Old Saxon *[[wurgian]], Old High German [[wurgen]] (German [[würgen]]).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/'wyrjan/}}

===Verb===
'''wyrġan''' (class 1 weak)
# to [[strangle]], [[throttle]], [[worry]]

